{
  "_readme": "CC0 plant models from Poly Haven (https://polyhaven.com), fetched 2026-07-19. Format: .gltf + external .bin + jpg textures (diff = albedo, nor_gl = OpenGL normal, arm = AO/roughness/metallic packed). Units are meters, Y-up, indexed triangles — matches engine conventions in docs/game/model-pipeline.md. NOTE: the engine loader (src/assets/mod.rs parse_gltf_mesh/load_gltf) uses only the FIRST mesh's FIRST primitive, so multi-mesh assets need repacking (see repack field per asset) before they render fully. REPACKED 2026-07-20: each asset's 'merged' field points at <slug>_merged.gltf (+ matching _merged.bin) produced by scripts/repack-plant-gltf.js — all meshes/primitives merged into one mesh/one primitive with node world transforms baked into positions/normals. *_merged.gltf is the ENGINE-FACING file; keep the originals as the source of truth and re-run the script if they change. SPLIT 2026-07-20: each asset also has a 'variants' list — <slug>_v1.gltf/.bin etc., one single-primitive file PER plant variant (clustered by world X/Z, base re-centered to x=0,z=0 with y untouched so y=0 stays ground), each carrying a minimal material that references the source textures/ folder base-color jpg by relative URI. Use variants for scatter/spawning (load via AssetManager::parse_gltf_mesh_with_texture, which also returns the RGBA8 base-color texture downscaled to <=1024); _merged keeps the whole side-by-side scene for reference. Single-primitive means ONE material per variant: multi-material variants carry the dominant-by-triangles material (saplings: twigs, so the ~500-tri trunk borrows the twig texture; potted plant: leaves, so pot/soil borrow the leaf texture — acceptable until a multi-primitive loader exists). Re-run: node scripts/repack-plant-gltf.js --split --all.",
